---
import Layout from '../../Base.astro';
import SimpleHero from '../../components/SimpleHero.astro';
import FeaturedArticles from "../../components/FeaturedArticles.astro";
import ServicesRelatedWork from "../../components/ServicesRelatedWork.astro";
import "../../styles/pages/_services-list.scss";
---

<Layout
	title='Custom Reporting & Analytics'
	description='Data is not useful if your team still does not know what to do next. We build reporting that turns scattered metrics into clear decisions about budget, content, and growth.'
>
	<SimpleHero tagline='Digital Marketing Services' title='Reporting' description="Data is not useful if your team still does not know what to do next. We build reporting that turns scattered metrics into clear decisions about budget, content, and growth." lottieFile='reporting.json' />
	<div class='service-body'>
		<div class='wrapper wrapper--narrow'>
			<h2>Where teams get stuck</h2>
			<p>Most businesses are not short on data. They are short on clarity. Metrics live in different platforms, dashboards answer the wrong questions, and reporting meetings end without a decision.</p>
			<p>That makes it hard to know what is actually working, what needs to change, and where the next dollar should go.</p>
			<h2>How we fix it</h2>
			<p>We start with the decisions your team needs to make, then build reporting around the signals that support those decisions. That can include campaign performance, channel trends, benchmarks over time, and the context needed to interpret the numbers correctly.</p>
			<p>The goal is not to hand over more charts. It is to give you a clearer read on what is happening and what should happen next.</p>
			<h2>What moving forward looks like</h2>
			<p>If you need reports your team will actually use, we can define the KPIs, consolidate the data, and turn each update into a clearer next move instead of another status document.</p>
			<p><a href='/contact/' class='button button--green'>Make Reporting Useful</a></p>
		</div>
		<ServicesRelatedWork tag={79} />
	</div>
	<FeaturedArticles />
</Layout>
